Program: Last Word
Title: David Storey, Ahmed Kathrada, Barbara Buss, Aloysius 'Lucky' Gordon
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b08k4zwf
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 2 Apr 2017
Matthew Bannister on Playwright and novelist David Storey who drew on his experiences as a professional rugby league player in some of his work. The South African anti apartheid activist Ahmed Kathrada who spent twenty six years in prison with Nelson Mandela and then became his parliamentary adviser. Barbara Buss who edited Woman Magazine in its 1970s heyday. And Lucky Gordon, the drug dealer, jazz singer and cook whose brief relationship with Christine Keeler led to the uncovering of the Profumo Affair in the 1960s. Producer: Neil George. Show less